  <text>
      <body>
         <head type="metadata"><name type="person" corresp="#WC">William Carey</name> to <addressee><name type="person">Samuel L. Clemens</name></addressee>
               <date when="1884-03-31">31 March 1884</date> &#x2022; <name type="place">New York, N.Y.</name>  
               <sourceline>(MS: CU-MARK, UCLC 41861)</sourceline></head>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
               <pb facs="carey01.jpg" xml:id="pb001" n="1"/>
               <opener>
                  <dateline rend="indentdateline"><name type="place">New York<space extent="2"/></name>    
               <lb/><date when="1884-03-31">Mch 31</date></dateline>
               <salute rend="noindent">Dear Sir:</salute>
            </opener>
               <p rend="text-indent:2">I am thinking of starting an autograph collection &amp; if you approve of the idea I shall be glad to have you send me a MS. If it has not been printed I will be very glad to share the expense of copyrighting it with you.</p>
               <p rend="text-indent:2">I would enclose a stamp but I do not wish to establish the precedent as I am just starting out. Please therefore pardon <pb facs="carey02.jpg" xml:id="pb002" n="2"/> the omission and this half sheet of paper. If you cannot spare a MS. a noble sentiment would be very gratefully received by</p>
               <closer><salute rend="indentcompclose">Yours very truly</salute>
                  <signed rend="indentsig">William Carey</signed>
                  <dateline rend="noindent">334 West 55<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> St
                     <lb/><space extent="2"/>N. Y. City</dateline>
               </closer>
            </div1>
            <div1 type="post-transmission">
               <div2 type="envelope">
                  <pb facs="carey-env.jpg" xml:id="pb003" n="3"/>
                  <ab>Samuel L. Clemens Esq | Hartford | Conn</ab>
                  <ab><note type="ed" xml:id="ed001" place="inline">postmarked, partially torn away:</note> <hi rend="xs-smallcaps">new <corr>york</corr> <gap reason="tornaway"/> g 84</hi></ab>
                  <ab><note type="ed" xml:id="ed002" place="inline">docketed by SLC, in pencil:</note> Carey</ab>
               </div2>
            </div1>
         <div1 xml:id="cm0001" type="commentary"/> 
      </body>
